    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors met or exceeded the required credibility level. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly scoped to static compression-bending under ASTM F1717 and no other loading regime is claimed. Quantitative output comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%) were satisfied for all three QoIs across N=11 specimens and two independent laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for this Class II device submission.",
